linux command :

1. mkdir - The mkdir command is used to create a new directory under any directory.

2. pwd - The pwd command is used to display the location of the current working directory.

3. rmdir - The rmdir command is used to delete a directory.

4. ls - The ls command is used to display a list of content of a directory.

5. cd - The cd command is used to change the current directory.

6. touch  - The touch command is used to create empty files. We can create multiple empty files by executing it once. 

7. rm - The rm command is used to remove a file.

8. cp - The cp command is used to copy a file or directory.

9. head - It displays the beginning of a file.

10. tail - It displays the last part of a file.

11. cat -  It displays all of the content which will be mentioned in files.

12. tac - It is opposite of cat. It displays from last part of the file.

